```{r}
library(tidyverse)
library(gapminder)
```

## Revist class exercises from Jan 20th, 2026
```{r}
my_gap <- gapminder
```

Using only the data for year 2007, create a table that reports the following for each continent in the my_gap dataset

The minimum, maximum and mean per capita GDP
The minimum, maximum and mean life expectancy
The number of countries in that continent

```{r}
gap_2007 <- my_gap %>% 
  filter(year == 2007) %>% 
  group_by(continent) %>% 
  summarise(min_gdp_percap = min(gdpPercap), 
            max_gdp_percap = max(gdpPercap),
            mean_gdp_percap = mean(gdpPercap),
            
            min_le = min(lifeExp),
            max_le = max(lifeExp),
            mean_le = mean(lifeExp),
            
            n_countries = n()
            
            )
```

```{r}
gap_2007
```

### NOAA precip exercise 
```{r}
precip_data <- read_csv("https://stahlm.github.io/ENS_215/Data/noaa_cag_state_precipitation.csv")
```


```{r}
precip_data <- precip_data %>% 
  select(YEAR, MONTH, STATE, Precip_inches = Value) %>% 
  filter(YEAR < 2025) %>% 
  mutate(MONTH = as.numeric(MONTH))
```



For your chosen state create a table that has
The monthly average precipitation (i.e. for January you would take the average of all the January data, for Febâ€¦)

Minimum observed precipitation for a given month
Maximum observed precipitation for a given month

```{r}
t1 <- precip_data %>% 
  #filter(STATE == "Florida") %>% 
  group_by(STATE, MONTH) %>% 
  summarize(avg_precip = mean(Precip_inches, na.rm = T),
            min_precip = min(Precip_inches, na.rm = T),
            max_precip = max(Precip_inches, na.rm = T)
            )

t1
```


